        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 10:31PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1030 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Chupadera Ranch Airport, or 27 miles southwest of Carrizo Springs.
This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, pea size hail and heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chupadera Ranch Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
